


### NYTimes
### String beans with Ginger and Garlic p. 260

* 2.5 lbs green beans, trimmed
* 1/4 cup vegetable oil
* 1/4 cup minced fresh ginger
* 4 medium garlic cloves

* Bring a large pot of water to boil
* fill a large bowl with ice water
* Boil beans until tender but crisp and bright green; start testing @ 4 minutes
* When done, plunge beans into ice water

* Heat 2 Tbsp oil in a skillet over high heat
* add half ingredients, cook until ginger and garlic soft and aromatic
* repeat with 2nd batch